(21, 1, '2015-11-05 05:35:15', '2015-11-05 05:35:15', 'This is an example page. It''s different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:\r\n<blockquote>Hi there! I''m a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my website. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pia coladas. (And gettin'' caught in the rain.)</blockquote>\r\n...or something like this:\r\n<blockquote>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</blockquote>\r\nAs a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href="http://127.0.0.1/boyer/wp-admin/">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!', 'Home Page', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '2-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-11-05 05:35:15', '2015-11-05 05:35:15', '', 2, 'http://127.0.0.1/boyer/index.php/2015/11/05/2-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(22, 1, '2015-11-05 09:06:16', '2015-11-05 09:06:16', 'In 1904, the Most Worshipful Grand Lodge of Washington granted a charter to each of <strong>Deer Park Lodge #134, </strong>and <strong>Chewelah Lodge #135</strong> located in the respective towns they wer named for. These were sponsored by <strong>Colville Lodge #50</strong>, and had operated under "dispensations", or by permission of the Grand Lodge for the previous year. The new lodge officers were duly installed, and each of the lodges opened under the new Charters and By-Laws. They have been very active successful for the past 107 years, serving the members and communities in the surrounding areas, 26 miles nearby to each other. In 2004, both lodges were rededicated in ceremonies by the MW Grand Lodge of Washington. In this time, each lodge had rented space for their Stated Meetings, in each location, moving only a very few times within the cities.\r\n\r\nSince 2010, each lodge faced difficult issues related to their meetings and locations, which resulted in the Chewelah Lodge to meet in the Deer Park Lodge hall (still a rented space). With much discussion and careful consideration by the officers and members of both lodges, an eventual conclusion came to decide to consolidate the lodges into one. This combines the considerable strengths of both lodges, ensuring a bright future for Masonry in the Chewelah, Deer Park area of Eastern Washington. The new lodge name is <span style="color: #ff0000;">Boyer Mountain Lodge #134</span>, named for a prominent peak that is halfway between Chewelah and Deer Park, in Eastern Washington.\r\n\r\nOne of the first action of the consolidated lodge hall, previously housing a church congregation. Please visit us, Mason or Visitor, to learn more and share in our Great Future!', 'Our Lodge History', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'our-lodge-history', '', '', '2015-11-05 09:06:16', '2015-11-05 09:06:16', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/boyer/?page_id=22', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(23, 1, '2015-11-05 21:29:16', '2015-11-05 21:29:16', 'Map &amp; Directions\r\n\r\nBoyer Mountain Lodge #134 of Washington\r\n\r\nPO Box 176\r\n\r\n310 N. Main Avenue\r\n\r\nDeer Park, WA 99006\r\n\r\nDirections from North:\r\n\r\nFirst Deer Park exit Left from HWY 395 at Dahl Road, past Mix Park to Main Avenue. Turn Right, then Left into the Lodge Hall parking.\r\n\r\nDirections from South:\r\n\r\nFirst Deer Park exit Right from HWY 395, past roundabout and North on Main Avenue. Past 4-way Stop, turn Right into the Lodge Hall parking.', 'Contact Us', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'contact-us', '', '', '2015-11-05 21:29:16', '2015-11-05 21:29:16', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/boyer/?page_id=23', 0, 'page', '', 0),
